    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00b0C/ 220\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate along with your<strong> ground paprika</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix it all together \u2013 this is your<strong> spice mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-wholemeal-wraps-with-chilli-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a splash of <strong>milk</strong> to a shallow bowl</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to another plate with the <strong>grated cheese</strong>, lots of<strong> pepper </strong>and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and mix it all together \u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-wholemeal-wraps-with-chilli-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> into 3 strips per person</p><p>Coat the <strong>fish strips </strong>in the <strong>spice mix</strong> (make sure to tap off any excess!)</p><p>Add the <strong>coated fish strips</strong> to the <strong>milk </strong>and finally press them into the <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs </strong>firmly to coat evenly \u2013 these are your <strong>breaded fish strips</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-wholemeal-wraps-with-chilli-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>breaded fish strips</strong> to the tray and top them with any <strong>remaining cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until cooked through and golden \u2013 these are your<strong> crispy fish strips</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-wholemeal-wraps-with-chilli-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fish strips are cooking, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and shred</p><p>Slice your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>finely into rounds</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-wholemeal-wraps-with-chilli-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>red chilli relish</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>mayo</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-wholemeal-wraps-with-chilli-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the fish strips are almost done, add your <strong>tortillas</strong> to a tray and put the tray in the oven for 1-2 min until warmed through (alternatively, add them to a plate and microwave!)</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-wholemeal-wraps-with-chilli-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide the<strong> sliced tomato</strong> and<strong> shredded lettuce</strong> evenly between the <strong>warmed tortillas</strong></p><p>Top each tortilla with a <strong>crispy fish strip </strong>and drizzle over the <strong>chilli mayo</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
